args:
Elisanne hands the captured priest over to the
Church and renounces her position as Paladyn.
The void dragon then appears and is reborn
by the purifying power of Elisanne's prayers.
But before they can celebrate, Ciella makes an
appearance and begins a decisive battle.
Just stay down, buddy. There's no need for\nanybody to die over this thing.
Yeah, we'll spare your miserable life...\nEVEN THOUGH YOU'RE A DIRTY RUMOR\nSPREADER PERSON!

Easy words! Yet when you people defeated
the Other, you spared no thought for what
would come after—for those like me who
found themselves without work or coin!

You mislead people with false rumors,
which is unacceptable. However, I also
understand you were doing what you felt
you had to do to survive.

When Dyrenell fell, the people who served
it were scattered and left to fend for
themselves—and I'm going to see that
made right.
You're coming with us, Father Marko.\nI want you to explain everything in\ndetail back at the Halidom.
If you wish to explain yourself, Father,\nnow is the time to lay facts out in full.
I have nothing to say to you.\nProceed with your judgment.
Though my life be forfeit, others will come\nafter to take up the cause and lead this\ncountry down a better path!
I see you've caught the charlatan pulling\nthe strings behind the scenes, and it was\nin fact the Church who was responsible.
I will take possession of the priest now.\nThe royal family will then conduct his trial\nand hand down appropriate judgment.
Father Marko serves the Goddess Ilia.\nThus, his judgment must be based on\nIlian doctrine.
By your leave, I will take him to the\nChurch and request an inquisitor.

You will do no such thing. This man has
besmirched the royal family, and it will
not do for us to leave his punishment up
to the whims of the Church.
Elisanne, we should hand him over.
If you take him, you'll only end up\nembroiled in an internal Church conflict.
Your position as a Paladyn could even be\nendangered. Do the smart thing here.
Do not worry yourself about such, Alex.
For after I give Father Marko over, I will\nrenounce my position as Grand Paladyn.
To be a Paladyn is your life's ambition!\nWhy would you throw it all away?!
I am sorry, Alex. But I have put much\nthought into this, and my mind is firm.
I am not adroit enough to both serve\nHis Highness and perform the duties\nrequired of a Paladyn.
As such, my loyalty to His Highness\nmust take precedence.
Are you certain of this choice, Elisanne?\nAre you certain you will not regret it?
.........\nThen if this be your path, you must walk it.

You would abandon your treasured position
and adhere to your beliefs? Impressive.
In that case, I withdraw my complaint
and remand the priest to your custody.
I am obliged to you, Prince Leonidas.\nAnd Your Highness...

I have made many and frequent mistakes.
After learning of the existence of that
historical document, I lost sight of both
my mission and my own beliefs.
Moving forward, I will no longer be a\nGrand Paladyn of the Ilian Church,\nbut your vassal entire.
And beyond that...I will be your friend.

Elisanne, are you SURE about this?
I think Alex is right: There's no need
for you to give up your position in the
Church over this.
In that case, I'll be counting on you\nmore than ever.
I shall not let you down again—not ever.\n...Now stand, Father Marko. I am taking\nyou to the Church to face judgment.
That was a void dragon's cry!
Confirming the presence of a single\ndragon in the nearby area.\n▷ It's coming, and fast!◁
Okay everyone, we're moving out!\nWe have to intercept that dragon!
This thing is WAY too close—the Halidom's\ngonna be at risk if we can't take it out!
Hang on! There's something strange\nabout this dragon. I can feel it.
It's as if it's suffering terribly...
You're right, darling. It's faint, but I can\nhear it trying to say something...
＂Help me...＂ Yes, that's it! The dragon is\nbeing tormented by black mana and needs\nour assistance!
If we could use holy power to purify the\nblack mana, we might be able to free it.
O Goddess Ilia, I beseech you,\nanswer my heartfelt prayer.
I bid you use your cleansing power to wash\nthe dragon free of corruption and darkness!
One more push, Zena! You got this!
Dammit! The thing went back to how it\nwas before! Maybe this ain't gonna work...
I can hear its voice no longer.
Even if I purify the black mana,\nthe miasma returns in short order.\nI may lack the power to do this.
Though I know not if it will be enough,\nlet us offer up a prayer together.
It will work—I know it will!
(No more hesitation—I believe in His\nHighness and the future he leads us to.)
(And I believe in myself, as well!)
I feel your mana flowing, Elisanne!\nIt is a pure and wonderful power!
O sacred mana, let your light flow over\nthis poor dragon and set it free!
Hot damn, ladies! Ya did it!
The dragon has returned to its\noriginal form!
Oh my gosh... Look at it!
Such a sublime form...\nSuch waves of pure water mana...
The dragon is standing down.\n▷And it's leaving! We were able\nto save it without harming it!◁
Indeed, it was your believing heart that\nnot only purified the dragon, but also\nallowed it to be reborn.
What an interesting spectacle that was.\nThank you for the amusement.
You certainly look as though a weight\nhas been lifted off your shoulders,\nformer Grand Paladyn.
I'm so delighted that you people finally\nfound the truth. Hopelessly late, but still.
Ciella, why are you trying to fight us?!
Don't misunderstand—I am fundamentally\nincompatible with you people.
The only way to establish a new justice\nand order is for the Ilian Church—and\nYOU—to disappear.
Have at you, Elisanne! Show me this\nvaunted ＂believing heart＂ of yours!
